Jay Stein admitted to practice before the United States  Supreme Court, the Northern, Central and Southern Federal District Courts of  California, and all California State Courts. 
                Education: 
Juris  Doctor, Northern Illinois University College of Law                 
                
                    • Dean’s List 
                    • Professor’s Research Assistant for law journal article, 
      Loyalty and the Limited Partnership, 34 U Kan L Rev 1 (1985)  
Bachelor  of Arts, Public Law, Northern Illinois University 
                        • Class Salutatorian 
                      • National Honor Society 
                      • Chief Justice, Student Supreme Court   


Practice Areas
 Intellectual  Property and Trade Secrets 
                Mr. Stein secures his  clients’ intellectual property rights, such as trademarks and copyrights,  through registration and licensing, and he protects them via enforcement before  the Trademark Trial and Appeal Board and in the Federal Courts.  Mr. Stein has developed expertise in  combating threats to his clients’ businesses posed by counterfeit goods and  also works with his clients to safeguard their trade secrets and proprietary  information.  In this  media-dominated business climate, protecting one’s brand is more critical than  ever and requires proactive and aggressive action.     
Business Counseling and Transactions 
  Developing  creative, but sound, business strategies and short-term and long-term planning  are Mr. Stein’s strengths.  By  becoming intimately familiar with his client’s business, Mr. Stein is able to  be most effective in rendering advice to his clients on the full spectrum of  business affairs, including business start-up, employment and consultancy  matters, supplier and customer relations, and consumer product regulation.  Mr. Stein devotes careful attention to  crafting each legal document uniquely to the particular business  transaction.  Envisioning the way  the transaction will ultimately play-out is the key to making the legal  documents “bullet-proof.”  
Antitrust and Competition  
                  In an increasingly  competitive business environment, making certain that a business’s competitors  play by the rules is critical.   Predatory pricing, false advertising and unfair competition are the  harms from which Mr. Stein protects his clients -- even against goliaths.  
Governmental Affairs and Public Relations 
   In  the last quarter-century since Mr. Stein, himself, served as an elected public  official, Mr. Stein has represented his clients’ interests before city  councils, county boards, and commissions on a variety of business and real  estate matters.  Mr. Stein  understands that success before such bodies is a function of both who you know  and how skilled your presentation is.    
Real Estate   
   Mr.  Stein has represented developers, property owners, real estate brokers,  mortgage companies, escrow agents, and appraisers in a wide array of real  property transactions and disputes, including those regarding subdivision  development, sales transactions, title issues, property line issues and  descriptions, easements, investments, and partnerships. 


Professional Activities
            
     Special  Master, appointed by State Bar of California (2002 – present) 
     Judge  Pro Tempore, Riverside County Municipal Court
     Arbitrator,  Riverside County 
     Member,  Corporate Law Departments Committee, State Bar of California (1997 – 2004)   
     Moderator  and Panelist, State Bar Conference MCLE Program, Trade Secret Protection;  
   The Danger of the Disloyal Employee (2003)  
     Contributor, Landlord-Tenant Handbook, Northern  Illinois University Press (1986)  

Civic Activities
    City Councilman, DeKalb,  Illinois (1983 – 1987)  
       Deputy  Voter Registrar, DeKalb County, Illinois (1983 – 1987) 
       Commissioner,  Water Resources Commission, DeKalb, Illinois (1983 – 1987) 
       Human  Relations Commission, DeKalb, Illinois (1984 – 1986) 
       Board  of Directors, Temple Emanuel (San Bernardino) (1994 – 1997)
       Board  of Directors; Vice President, Jewish Family Services (1998 -  2007)
       Board  of Directors, Holmby Westwood Property Owners Association (2009 –  present)
      Member, Task Force on Complementary Jewish  Education, BJELA (2012 – present)  
 






 
